<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="HertiageWalks.Views.InfoPage">

    <ContentPage.Content>
        <StackLayout>

            <Label Text="Information Help Page"
                VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" 
                HorizontalOptions="CenterAndExpand" />
            <Label Text="Trails" VerticalOptions="Center" HorizontalOptions="Center"/>
            <Label VerticalOptions="Center"
                HorizontalOptions="Center" >
                <Label.Text>
                    When viewing a trail, there will be three buttons available to be pressed on the screen.
                    The first button is to Play/Pause the associated audio file. This audio file includes an audio version of the trail description.
                    The second button opens the Map and displays each of the stops within the trail as markers on the map, to make them easy to locate.
                    The third button displays a list of all of the stops that are a part of the trail and allow you to view data about the individual stop.
                </Label.Text>
            </Label>
            <Label Text="Stops" VerticalOptions="Center" HorizontalOptions="Center"/>
            <Label VerticalOptions="CenterAndExpand" HorizontalOptions="CenterAndExpand">
                <Label.Text>
                    The individual stops each have their own image, description and audio file. This includes a button to play the audio file, as well as a text version of the description.
                </Label.Text>
            </Label>
        </StackLayout>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>